thread.title: SE Portland woman injured in early morning fire

author: Noelle Crombie | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: SE Portland woman injured in early morning fire
text:
A woman was hospitalized early Thursday after an early morning kitchen fire burned her face and chest, Portland fire officials said.
Firefighters responded to reports of a fire at about 5 a.m. at a house in the 2200 block of Southeast 51st Avenue. They found a small kitchen fire had been extinguished.
The cause remains under investigation.
The woman, who was not identified, was taken to Legacy Emanuel Medical Center.
-- The Oregonian
